WEBVTT

00:00.495 --> 00:02.779
You feel like trying
something new for dinner?

00:02.780 --> 00:05.081
Maybe Indian, Tex-Mex?

00:05.083 --> 00:07.217
You ever wonder how
humans would be different

00:07.219 --> 00:10.420
if they evolved from lizards
instead of mammals?

00:12.456 --> 00:14.674
Okay, let's talk
about that.

00:16.093 --> 00:18.812
As you know, lizards--
cold-blooded animals--

00:18.814 --> 00:20.897
lack the ability to
sense temperature.

00:20.899 --> 00:23.817
But they do move more
sluggishly when it's cold.

00:23.819 --> 00:26.486
So, lizard weathermen
would say things like,

00:26.488 --> 00:29.772
"Bring a sweater,
it's slow outside."

00:31.775 --> 00:34.861
I love my mind.

00:34.863 --> 00:36.412
We all do.

00:36.414 --> 00:37.813
Now, how about dinner?

00:37.815 --> 00:42.035
Oh, I would assume we'd enjoy
insects or smaller lizards.

00:42.037 --> 00:44.037
We could also pull each other's
tails off and grill them;

00:44.039 --> 00:46.039
they'll just grow back.

00:48.759 --> 00:49.825
Oh!

00:49.827 --> 00:53.713
My life-size cardboard
Mr. Spock is here!

00:53.715 --> 00:57.350
I know he wouldn't care for
an outburst of human emotion,

00:57.352 --> 01:00.186
but, oh, goodie, oh,
goodie, oh, goodie.

01:01.505 --> 01:06.676
Commander Spock requesting
permission to be unfolded.

01:06.678 --> 01:07.677
Excuse me.

01:07.679 --> 01:10.179
Permission granted, Commander.

01:11.782 --> 01:14.367
Which is why the more
intelligent the monkey,

01:14.369 --> 01:16.986
the more feces they fling.

01:18.489 --> 01:20.456
(knocks)
Excuse me, Amy.

01:20.458 --> 01:22.492
Penny, do you have plans
for dinner tonight?

01:22.494 --> 01:23.859
Why, you guys going somewhere?

01:23.861 --> 01:24.994
No, I mean just you and me.

01:24.996 --> 01:28.248
You mean, like a date?

01:28.250 --> 01:30.166
Not like a date, a date.

01:30.168 --> 01:34.337
Ooh...!
Ooh...!

01:34.339 --> 01:38.341
Um... o-okay.

01:38.343 --> 01:39.342
Sure.

01:39.344 --> 01:42.979
Ooh...!
Ooh...!

01:42.981 --> 01:44.230
SHELDON:
Oh, no!

01:44.232 --> 01:47.283
They sent the wrong Spock!

01:48.402 --> 01:52.021
Live long and suck it,
Zachary Quinto.

01:52.022 --> 01:54.222
